\le -\ell_i^{(\hat{t}-1)}
= \frac{1}{1+e^{y_{i,2}f(\mathbf{W}^{D,(\hat{t}-1)},\mathbf{x}_{i,2})}}
\le \frac{1}{1+e^{\frac{1}{m}\sum_{r=1}^m \rho_{y_{i,2},r,i,2}^{D,(\hat{t}-1)}-\kappa D/2}}.
\]
The result is obvious since \( \frac{1}{m}\sum_{r=1}^m \rho_{y_{i,2},r,i,2}^{D,(\hat{t}-1)} \) is bounded. Since then we complete the proof. ‚ñ°

Proof of Proposition E.1. We prove it by induction. When \(t=0\), all results hold obviously. Now, we suppose there exists \(\hat{t}\) and all the results hold for \(t\le \hat{t}-1\). Next, we prove these results hold at \(t=\hat{t}\).

First, for the first result, when \(j\neq y_{i,2}\), we have \(\bar{\rho}_{j,r,i,2}^{D,(\hat{t})}=0\). When \(j=y_{i,2}\), by the update rule, it holds that
\[
\bar{\rho}_{j,r,i,2}^{D,(\hat{t})}
= \bar{\rho}_{j,r,i,2}^{D,(\hat{t}-1)}
- \frac{\eta}{N_2 m}\,\ell_i^{(\hat{t}-1)}\cdot \sigma'\!\left(\langle \mathbf{w}_{j,r}^{D,(\hat{t}-1)},\boldsymbol{\xi}_{i,2}\rangle\right)\cdot \|\boldsymbol{\xi}_{i,2}\|_2^2. \tag{E.13}
\]
If \(\bar{\rho}_{j,r,i,2}^{D,(\hat{t}-1)}\le 2\log(T^{**})\), we have
\[
\bar{\rho}_{j,r,i,2}^{D,(\hat{t})}
\le \bar{\rho}_{j,r,i,2}^{D,(\hat{t}-1)} + \frac{\eta}{N_2 m}\frac{3\sigma_{p,2}^2 d}{2}
< 2\log(T^{**}) + \log(T^{**}) < 4\log(T^{**}),
\]
where the first inequality uses the fact \(-1\le \ell_i^{(\hat{t}-1)}\le 0\) and Lemma C.1, and the second inequality is by the condition of \(\eta\) in Condition 4.1. If \(\bar{\rho}_{j,r,i,2}^{D,(\hat{t}-1)}\ge 2\log(T^{**})\), from (E.13) we know that \(\bar{\rho}_{j,r,i,2}^{D,(t)}\) increases with \(t\). Therefore, suppose that \(t_{j,r,i,2}\) is the last time satisfying \(\bar{\rho}_{j,r,i,2}^{D,(t_{j,r,i,2})}\le 2\log(T^{**})\). Now, we want to show that the increment of \(\bar{\rho}_{j,r,i,2}^D\) from \(t_{j,r,i,2}\) to \(\hat{t}\) does not exceed \(2\log(T^{**})\):
\[
\begin{aligned}
\bar{\rho}_{j,r,i,2}^{D,(\hat{t})}
&= \bar{\rho}_{j,r,i,2}^{D,(t_{j,r,i,2})}
- \frac{\eta}{N_2 m}\,\ell_i^{(t_{j,r,i,2})}\cdot \sigma'\!\left(\langle \mathbf{w}_{j,r}^{D,(t_{j,r,i,2})},\boldsymbol{\xi}_{i,2}\rangle\right)\cdot \|\boldsymbol{\xi}_{i,2}\|_2^2 \\
&\quad - \sum_{t_{j,r,i,2}<t<\hat{t}-1} \frac{\eta}{N_2 m}\,\ell_i^{(t)}\cdot \sigma'\!\left(\langle \mathbf{w}_{j,r}^{D,(t)},\boldsymbol{\xi}_{i,2}\rangle\right)\cdot \|\boldsymbol{\xi}_{i,2}\|_2^2. \tag{E.14}
\end{aligned}
\]
Here, the second term can be bounded as
\[
\left|\frac{\eta}{N_2 m}\,\ell_i^{(t_{j,r,i,2})}\cdot \sigma'\!\left(\langle \mathbf{w}_{j,r}^{D,(t_{j,r,i,2})},\boldsymbol{\xi}_{i,2}\rangle\right)\cdot \|\boldsymbol{\xi}_{i,2}\|_2^2\right|
\le \frac{3\eta\sigma_{p,2}^2 d}{2N_2 m}\le \log(T^{**}),
\]
where the first inequality is by Lemma C.1 and the second inequality is by the condition of \(\eta\) in Condition 4.1. For the third term, note that when \(t>t_{j,r,i,2}\),
\[
\begin{aligned}
\langle \mathbf{w}_{y_{i,2},r}^{D,(t)},\boldsymbol{\xi}_{i,2}\rangle
&\ge \langle \mathbf{w}_{y_{i,2},r}^{D,(T^*+1)},\boldsymbol{\xi}_{i,2}\rangle
+ \bar{\rho}_{j,r,i,2}^{D,(t)}
- 16N_2 \sqrt{\frac{\log\!\left(4(N_1^2+N_2^2)/\delta\right)}{d}}\,\log(T^{**}) \\
&\ge -2\sqrt{\log(12mN_2/\delta)}\cdot \sigma_0\sigma_{p,2}\sqrt{d}
+ 2\log(T^{**})
- 16\!\left(N_1\frac{\sigma_{p,2}}{\sigma_{p,1}} + N_2\right)\!
\sqrt{\frac{\log\!\left(4(N_1^2+N_2^2)/\delta\right)}{d}}\,\log(T^{**}) \\
&\ge 1.8\log(T^{**}). \tag{E.15}
\end{aligned}
\]
